Bug 2051476 - Normalize file URIs from command-line attachments. r=darktrojan

When external applications pass attachments via `-compose`, they sometimes use
URL-encoded Windows paths such as `file:///C%3A%5Ctemp%5Cinfo.pdf`. The backend
correctly resolved these to native files, but `ComposeStartup` stored the raw
`uri.spec` — preserving percent-encoded backslashes in the URL string.

This broke the UI's filename extraction (`attachment.url.split("/").pop()`),
since there are no forward slashes in a `%5C`-delimited path.

Fix by rebuilding `attachment.url` from the resolved native file path via
`PathUtils.toFileURI()`, which produces a standard-compliant URI with forward
slashes regardless of the input form. Non-file URIs continue to use `uri.spec`.

Also add marionette tests for the `--compose` attachment code path, covering:
- a single file with a comma in the name (exercises the comma-in-URI fix from
  bug 900117)
- multiple comma-separated file URIs
- that the resulting `attachment.url` is a well-formed `file:///` URI

Differential Revision: https://phabricator.services.mozilla.com/D310203


